dt: {bc}any of a class (Diplopoda) of myriapod arthropods having usually a cylindrical segmented body covered with hard integument, two pairs of legs on most apparent segments, and unlike centipedes no poison fangs

et: Latin {it}millepeda{/it}, a small crawling animal, from {it}mille{/it} thousand + {it}ped-, pes{/it} foot {ma}{mat|foot|}{/ma}
shortdef: any of a class (Diplopoda) of myriapod arthropods having usually a cylindrical segmented body covered with hard integument, two pairs of legs on most apparent segments, and unlike centipedes no poison fangs
